cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep learning architecture for synthesizing sensory data and uses a deep learning based discriminator model for distinguishing between the true and synthesized data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with data privacy and security, which suggests the sub-categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely options. The use of sensor data and the focus on preserving statistical properties of the real data suggest the sub-categories cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
